7, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His family had to stop eating at restaurants because of the crowds.\", \"from\": 5078, \"to\": 5145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He signed thousands of autographs, starred inSPRINT, flashed Yu-Gi-Oh!\", \"from\": 5146, \"to\": 5216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"cards, and wore a bright red running suit and white pearls.\", \"from\": 5217, \"to\": 5276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he entered Hayward Field at the trials, Snoop was carrying his bag stuffed with his gear.\", \"from\": 5277, \"to\": 5371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He then won the 100 and the 200 to qualify, loudly and speedily, for Paris.\", \"from\": 5372, \"to\": 5447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5441, \"end\": 5446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.884761056043172e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He discussed adding the 4X400.\", \"from\": 5448, \"to\": 5478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were 400-meter specialists from the U.S. who didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t much care for Lyles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s volunteering for that relay in Paris.\", \"from\": 5480, \"to\": 5601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5595, \"end\": 5600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.884761056043172e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And there were track aficionados who scoffed when he labeled himself, onSPRINT, the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fastest man.\", \"from\": 5602, \"to\": 5708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some Jamaican athletes and fans argued that Lyles had flared existing issues with comments (his girlfriend, Junelle Bromfield, is a Jamaican sprinter) voiced in public and more than once.\", \"from\": 5709, \"to\": 5896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5714, \"end\": 5722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999999914543878, \"rank\": 8.545842797485226e-09, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 5753, \"end\": 5758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7652086834710999, \"rank\": 0.30682580981056595, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 5817, \"end\": 5834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Junelle_Bromfield\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Junelle Bromfield\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Junelle_Bromfield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Junelle_Bromfield\"}, {\"begin\": 5841, \"end\": 5849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999999914543878, \"rank\": 8.545842797485226e-09, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles was overconfident, to put it kindly, or arrogant.\", \"from\": 5897, \"to\": 5952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He violated the sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s unwritten codes.\", \"from\": 5953, \"to\": 5995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But nothing Lyles said was mean, cruel or delusional.\", \"from\": 5997, \"to\": 6050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6009, \"end\": 6014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.7652086834710999, \"rank\": 0.30682580981056595, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a basis for everything he said.\", \"from\": 6051, \"to\": 6092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heisthe fastest man in the world at the moment.\", \"from\": 6093, \"to\": 6140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He may still be after Paris, too.\", \"from\": 6141, \"to\": 6174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6163, \"end\": 6168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.884761056043172e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But his comments, true as they were, did not especially endear him to the insular community of track and field.\", \"from\": 6175, \"to\": 6286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Noah is just trying to understand himself, and the more he understands about himself, the faster he runs.\", \"from\": 6287, \"to\": 6396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6291, \"end\": 6295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"score\": 0.9996239095009498, \"rank\": 0.00037022851452198075, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the faster he runs, the larger the spotlight.\", \"from\": 6398, \"to\": 6447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And should he accomplish everything he plans, the spotlight will soon get much larger.\", \"from\": 6449, \"to\": 6535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Vintage Noah Lyles story No.\", \"from\": 6537, \"to\": 6565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"3: Keisha recalls one time, when Noah was young, he asked for green food coloring and he got mad when she didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have any.\", \"from\": 6566, \"to\": 6690, \"entiti